> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Wash and dry produce. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp} and 1 TBSP @sugar{1%tsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until dissolved.

Add @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} and half the cilantro; mix until well combined. Set aside, tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until turkey is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @pho stock concentrate{1}, @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), and as much @sriracha{1%tsp} as you like. Mix until thoroughly combined; taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

While turkey cooks, in a #small bowl{}, stir together @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, about ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with hoisin turkey and slaw (draining first). Drizzle with lime mayo; garnish with remaining cilantro and a squeeze of lime juice. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.